<http://www.spektrix.com/ticketseller/event/26601APLTNSPSGDPBRQVGGSRDMVBVVNQK> a schema:Event;
  schema:name "TENILLE TOWNES in Concert";
  schema:description """
	$89 Per Person<span><br/></span>Limited VIP Packages Available! <span class=\"BoldText\">SOLD OUT!</span><span><br/></span>Including fees & charges<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>For<span class=\"BoldText\">Tenille Townes</span>, writing songs is a way of reaching out to anyone longing to make sense of a wildly confusing world.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">UPDATE!</span>Tenille has just released a new song out now, featuring<span class=\"BoldText\">Lori McKenna</span>, and with her new album The Acrobat coming April 10th! Visit: TenilleTownes.com<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>In the last five years alone, the Canada-born artist’s full-hearted and soul-searching songwriting has led to touring with legends including<span class=\"BoldText\">Stevie Nicks, Miranda Lambert, Shania Twain</span>and many more; as well as collaborations with<span class=\"BoldText\">Bryan Adams</span>and<span class=\"BoldText\">Train</span>. Propelled by her hits Somebody’s Daughter (Music Canada certified Platinum, RIAA certified Gold); and Jersey on the Wall (I’m Just Asking) (Music Canada certified Gold), Tenille has taken home two<span class=\"BoldText\">JUNO Awards</span>, (“Country Album of the Year” 2021 & 2023) —all while building up a globe-spanning fan base irresistibly drawn to her live performances and intensely honest storytelling.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>With her many accolades, also including<span class=\"BoldText\">17 Canadian Country Music Association Awards</span>, (“Entertainer of the Year”; “Female Artist of the Year” 2019-2022; “Album of the Year” for The Lemonade Stand and Masquerades); and two<span class=\"BoldText\">Academy of Country Music Awards</span>, (“New Female Artist of the Year” & “Music Event of the Year”); the now Nashville-based, risen star begins a bold new chapter with her most fully realized work to date: a gorgeously sculpted collection of songs that bring a moodier and more unfettered sound to her compassionate lyrical outpouring.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Don’t miss<span class=\"BoldText\">Tenille Townes</span>, an intimate, unforgettable VDPAC Signature Concert Series experience, with Special Guest,<span class=\"BoldText\">Chris Buck</span>!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Tenille Townes – The Acrobat</span>(NEW Album! The Acrobat drops April 10th)<span><br/></span>
""";
